'''Rajit Kapur''' ([[Hindi]]: à¤°à¤à¤¿à¤¤ à¤à¤ªà¥à¤°, [[Urdu]]: Ø±Ø¬ÙØª Ú©Ù¾ÙØ±) is an [[India]]n actor. He is particularly known for his award-winning portrayal of [[Mahatma Gandhi]] in the 1996 film, ''[[The Making of the Mahatma]]''. One of his most popular stints is his portrayal of [[Byomkesh Bakshi]] in a television series of the same name based on the character created by [[Sharadindu Bandyopadhyay]] and directed by [[Basu Chatterjee]]. He is also known for his acting in the Malayalam film "Agni Sakshi".
==Career== Rajit Kapur has been a favourite of renowned Indian film director [[Shyam Benegal]], featuring in a number of his films till date. He has been part of the trilogy of Shyam Benegal- [[Mammo]](1994), [[Sardari Begum]] (1996) and [[Zubeidaa]] (2001). Of these the most famous has been [[Zubeidaa]], written by [[Khalid Mohammed]].
Kapur plays the role of the son of the title character in [[Zubeidaa]]. The film is shown mostly as a flashback with Kapur being the narrator. The film went on to win the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Hindi]].
The other renowned films he had worked in are [[Ghulam]], [[Bose: The Forgotten Hero]] and [[Suraj Ka Satvan Ghoda]]. [[Suraj Ka Satvan Ghoda]] was a 1992 film, again directed by [[Benegal]], based on the novel of the same name by [[Dharmavir Bharati]]. It won the 1993 [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Hindi]].
Kapur has also been active in theatre as an actor as well as director.
